  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And it came to pass, that when David was come to the top of the mount,.... Of the mount of Olives: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "where he worshipped God; by prayer and praise; here very probably he composed and sung the third psalm Psa 3:1, which, as the title shows, was made when he fled from Absalom: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "behold, Hushai the Archite came to meet him, with his coat rent, and earth upon his head; in token of mourning, and as a bringer of bad tidings, see 2 Samuel 1:2; perhaps he was an inhabitant of Archi, at least originally, which lay on the borders of the tribe of Ephraim, Joshua 16:2; from whence he had his name. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "behold, Hushai the Archite came to meet him, with his coat rent, and earth upon his head; in token of mourning, and as a bringer of bad tidings, see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 1:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; perhaps he was an inhabitant of Archi, at least originally, which lay on the borders of the tribe of Ephraim, ",
